data.value: When building an MTG deck to play, typically you will start out building a simple 60 card deck that contains on average 23 lands and 37 non-land cards to begin with. When building a deck like this typically only 4 copies of any specific card can be put into one deck at a time with the exemption of basic lands. Like in the deck image to the side sometimes you only put 1 or 2 copies of a given card in the deck to meet the deck requirements. Once you have put together what you think you would like to play in the colors you have chosen, check the different costs to play all your cards and decide whether or not you want to put more or less lands into the deck comparing how expensive some of the cards are to play. On a typical curve for the game you would want to keep 23 lands, but if the costs of the cards are higher you may want to put more in and take out some cards you don’t think you need.
